comments.body:
@idvoretskyi There's some sort of subcommand difference depending on what version of openstackclient you're using. @xsgordon is the one who ran into the bug, they'll have more details.

No matter what, we are going to have to prescribe a specific version of openstackclient to make sure this works. The individual commands(heat, swift, nova, etc) appear to have more stable arguments and flags. However there were concerns about them being deprecated, and indeed in the most recent versions of the individual commands a huge, distracting deprecation notice was displayed every time a command was issued.

There will always be restrictions for the version of the client, and the restrictions are listed in the documentation, and SHOULD in the future be checked by this provider.

